comment: The data records are arrays of length 5 or 6.
The first four entries of each record are the character name,
the character position, the degree of the character field,
and a string describing the OD.
The last entry is a string that lists how the OD was computed,
as a comma separated sequence of flags.
For non-simple groups in characteristic 2,
the record has length 6, and position 5 describes whether
the matrix group embeds in the simple orthogonal group (value S+)
or not (value S-).
The flags listed in the last column mean the following:
- AGR: verified using the Atlas of Group Representations
- RP: verified using a representations constructed by Richard Parker
- const(<rep>): verified using a constituent of the reduction of <rep>
(a permutation representation from the AGR)
- order: group order divides the order of only one relevant O+/O- group
- permchar: chi+1 is a 2-trans. permutation character
- lift: the p-modular OD arises from the ordinary OD
- lift(+...): the p-modular OD arises from the ordinary OD and known ODs
- ev: there is a group element without eigenvalues +-1
- ext(...): the OD of the restriction to a subgroup is known
- rest(...): the character is the restriction from an overgroup
- specht: verified using the Jantzen-Schaper formula

- syl(

): verified by orth. stable restriction to a Sylow

-subgroup
